{"word":"ἐνιαύσιος","slug":"ἐνιαύσιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐνιαύσιος</b></el> <el>(ἐνιαύσιος, η, ον) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of a year, one year old</i>, <el>σῦς</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>yearly, annual, year by year</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>for a year, lasting a year</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <el>κἀνιαύσιος βεβώς</el> gone, absent <i>for a year</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ἐνιαυτός'><el>ἐνιαυτός</el></a>\n"}]}